reviews.text: Perfect joint for local Cantonese food. Place and decor only so so. Food is tasty though. Remember to ask for "DONG DONG", the lady boss. Take her advice for the day special. You wouldn't be far off.

Great pot rice, chicken and daily soup. Price is reasonable. Fish also delicious. Very popular but don't go Friday or Saturday or Sunday evening dinners. Long long lineups. Other nights are usually ok.
Awful service. I went there just by myself and told that they are fully booked even though there are some small tables available. They shouldn’t be listed on the Michelin guide. Disgusting service.
Only be there if you are looking for good food but not the renovation. Expensive if you ordered the recommended daily special which is not on the menu.

A truly No MSG Chinese restaurant. 
No nonsense  Good food. Fresh ingredients.
